봉준호 작품들도 그렇지만 우리나라 작품들의 해학적인 부분을  서양인들이 잘 이해 못하더라고요. 진지하다가 왜 갑자기 웃긴게 나오냐는 반응은 서양인들에게 알려진 한국 영상물에서 언제나  나오는 것 같아요.

Spoilers: Just things I noticed throughout Season 1


1) The spy who is giving away information on the Prince. It seems like it might be his bodyguard since it started from the palace, but looking forward to seeing where they take that.


2) Seems like the Prince's Bodyguard sent his wife to the palace and is now housed with all the other pregnant women.... Who else thinks she will be the one with the male child that gets taken by the Empress, to be the new Crown Prince?! And if he is the spy, that would be very ironic... lol


3)I wonder if they will have flashbacks of whatever happened three years before. By some of the things they were saying something similar seems to have happened before, but perhaps on a smaller scale.


4) I also hope they give more background on some of the characters like Seobi. The mysterious gunman, while they have spoken about him a bit and even had a small flashback, most of his story is still a mystery.


5) Definitely looking forward to seeing more of the story behind the human bad guys. AKA: the queen and her dad. Dad seems to be oblivious of his daughter not really being pregnant. So I wonder if she is looking to break free from Dad too.

In case you see this, people who made this:

I am from the Netherlands and I am hugely impressed by the series.

We have all seen so many zombie stories. You took everything that's stupid and annoying about them and got rid of them. (Everything explodes the first day, military fails immediately, nobody uses their communication tactics/technology, everyone dies stupidly, people are stupid heroes without reason and get themselves or others killed by accident, people immediately start killing each other over some old beans or bs like that) + You added the whole element of being in old times (shown by excessive use of fascinating old tech and culture) and the whole political struggle.. Truly fascinating..

The zombies are realistic, the strategies (political and tactical) are fascinating and the cinematography is beautiful. The acting, the script, even the extras are amazing.

I love everything about it.

Also it's a truly a breath of fresh air to see Koreans instead another American zombie story on screen.

You truly took it to another level.

I am thankful to have viewed this great story and I am looking forward to the next season.

이영상에서는 조선시대 남자들의 모자만 나오지만 조선시대 여성들도 추운 겨울이나 여름,
예복을 입을때나 외출을 할때 모자를 썻다. 일단 조선시대의 돌이 지나고 4~5살 밖에 안된 여자아이들은 굴레 라는 모자를 썻다.(남자 아이들이 쓰는 경우도 있다)
굴레는 현재 북한 개성지방 에서 혼례를 할때 신부가 족두리 나 화관 대신 쓴다.
굴레 말고도 조선시대 여성들은 남바위 라는 모자도 썻다(남바위는 남녀 모두 쓸수 있는 모자다) 당시 조선시대 여성들은 겨울에는 볼끼 라는 모자를 썻다,그리고 당시의 여성들은 외출을 할때 얼굴을 가려야 하는데 이때 너울 이라는 모자를 써서 얼굴을 가렸다.
또 조선시대에는 아얌 이라는 겨울용 모자도 있는데 조선초기에는 남녀공용 이었으나 후기에는 여자들만 쓸수 있었다. 아얌은 가체의 유행이 사그라든 순조때에 서민부녀자들이 착용했고 서부지방에서는 기생들이 썻고 예복을 입을떄 쓰기도 했다
아양 떨다 라는 말도 아얌이라는 모자에서 유래 되었다.
그외에 장옷. 전모. 조바위. 족두리. 화관도 조선시대 여성들이 외출을 하거나 혼례를 치르거나 예복을 입을때 착용했다.

집안에서 모자쓰는건 실제 역사나 실제와는 다른 부분이 있다는겁니다.
그리고 조선시대는 양반,중인,상민,천민 이렇게 네 계급이 나뉘어져 있었는데 양반과 중인은 외출이나 업무시 꼭 자신의 신분이나 계급,직업에 맞는 모자가 각각 따로 있었고 저마다 불리우는 이름도 따로 있었죠.그리고 음 그 깃털은 사실 특히 무관들의 계급을 상징하는데 직위가 높아질수록 모자의 크기나 깃털이 화려하고 커지며 고급스러워지죠.
꿩털에서 매의 깃털까지.
재밌는점은 매의 털은 워낙 고가라 구하지못하면 걍 모조품으로 대체했다는 일화도 있는걸보면 예나 지금이나 역시 돈이 중요하단 사실..
암튼 조선이 모자의 천국,모자의 나라인것은 사실이었던걸로 보입니다.
그건 100년전 서양인이 본 조선이라는 몇몇 조선을 거쳐간 서양인들의 저서에도 나오는 부분이고 정작 오늘날 한국인들도 잘 모르는 사실중에 하나는
조선의 그 수많은 모자들이 고종이 헤이그에 밀사를 파견하던 당시 그즈음의 파리에서 열린 세계박람회?에서 조선의 당시 모자들과 한복등이 소개되었는데 이게 서구권에게 신선한 충격으로 다가왔고 패션하면 프랑스란 말이 아마 그때나 이전부터 나왔듯이 모자나 패션부분에서 디자이너들에게 어느정도 영감과 영향을 주어 서구권에서도 이미 백여년전에 응용되었다는 부분입니다.
적어도 프랑스 패션에는 그때부터 어느정도 영향을 끼쳤는데 특히 모자의 다양성과 디자인의 창의성에서.
이게 서구문화에 흡수된건데 이런 부분에 대해선 사실 좀더 디테일한 연구나 고증이 필요한 부분이긴해도 결국 문화는 돌고도는거라는걸 실감하게 해줍니다.
이젠 킹덤이란 드라마가 그런일을 한몫 담당하는군요.

Just finished this series and I am blown away. So sharing some of my thoughts:
- My take is that Lord Ahn Hyeon may be a secondary antagonist, behind Minister Cho. I think Lord Ahn Hyeon may have used the resurrection plant to resurrect his mother 3 years ago when she died (and he placed her in the cave, where there were the shackles to hold her in place - which the physician saw in the last episode). And they probably first tested the potential of the plant on the Sumang villagers - and I wonder if it ties in with how Lord Ahn Hyeon was able to defeat 30,000 Japanese soldiers with only 500 men.

- The fact that Minister Cho mentions that Lord Ahn Hyeon can never cross him, and when he told the physician to do what he did 3 years ago - is probably proof that he helped cover up what Lord Ahn Hyeon did.

- I also found it interesting because Lord Ahn Hyeon seemed to be such a great father figure (and the kind you wouldn't expect to be corruptible) to the Crown Prince when he was young.

- There's also an interesting point that the Physician Lee made in the shed before he turned into a monster himself. He said "It wasn't like this in Hanyang. When Dan-i was bitten, he spent days being sick and died as a human being. When these people got bitten, they turned into the same monster." I still can't put my finger on this point - apparently something happened in Hanyang (probably during the process of resurrecting someone? Is it the Emperor?) that was different than how the monsters are now.

 - Similar to popular opinion, I predict the guard's wife will be the one to give birth to a son and be held hostage or worse, killed.

- I think the Cho magistrate will man up and save the physician from the monsters in the Frozen Valley. I think he's a rather dynamic funny character (great acting!) - comes from the corrupt clan, make morally-questionable mistakes - but has great potential for redemption in the end.

Ah, so many dynamics - I certainly can't wait for season 2.
